result.value: Frontend for the DataCite DOI Fabrica service
The web frontend for the DataCite Fabrica service for managing DataCite providers, repositories, prefixes and DOIs.

result.name: Form changes
result.description:
This release is a combination of fixes plus slight changes to prevent potential problems.

Includes:
* Fix for title/description not allow validation due to being perceived empty
* By default the form is disabled for all DOI's created outside the form itself, this is to prevent accidental metadata changes.
* DataCite staff can enable form editing manually in specific usecases.

result.description:
Changes in this release:

* use [polyfill.io](https://polyfill.io/v2/docs/) to better support Internet Explorer 11 (#13)
* fixed bugsnag configuration for error reporting (#28)
* handle external links in different browser window, or in a browser if using the App (#32)

* fixed error showing the wrong DOI count in overview charts (datacite/datacite#246)

result.name: Bracco v.0.9.22
result.description: * [#30](https://github.com/datacite/bracco/issues/30): disabled typeahead in search, as it was sometimes swallowing entered characters. Search is now triggered by `enter` or by clicking the `Search` button.

result.name: Bracco v.0.9.20
result.description:
This is the first version of DOI Fabrica that is also built as an App. Use at your own risk, and provide feedback via support@datacite.org.

This release is Mac-only and comes as a (very large) Mac installer application.

You will need the following things properly installed on your computer.

- [Git](https://git-scm.com/)
- [Node.js](https://nodejs.org/) (with NPM) - 18.x
- [Ember CLI](https://ember-cli.com/) - 3.24
- [Yarn Classic](https://classic.yarnpkg.com/) - 1.29.x

- `yarn ember serve`
- Visit your app at [http://localhost:4200](http://localhost:4200).
Make use of the many generators for code, try `ember help generate` for more details

- `npm run lint:hbs`
- `npm run lint:js`
- `npm run lint:js -- --fix`
The application as Docker containers via GitHub Actions and AWS Fargate.

- Fork the project
- Write tests for your new feature or a test that reproduces a bug
- Implement your feature or make a bug fix
- Do not mess with Rakefile, version or history
- Commit, push and make a pull request. Bonus points for topical branches.
